Package com.company

package com.company
  • Class
    Description
    Architecture
    Architecture is the abstract base class for all things that can be constructed on a street and has properties of position, length, and height and has a functionality of being focused on.
    Building
    Building is the abstract base class for all things that are architecture and have an owner.
    Color
    Color is a class for representing colors and consists of red, green, blue, and alpha channel integer values in range of 0 to 255 including.
    Focused
    Focused is the interface for all the architectures to add them the functionality to be focused on.
    Heighted
    Heighted is the interface for all objects that have height property.
    House
    House is the subclass of the Building that has unique properties of number of rooms and color.
    Lengthed
    Lengthed is the interface for all the objects that have length as property.
    Main
    Main class.
    Market
    Market is the subclass of the building that has an opening and a closing time properties.
    Office
    Office is the subclass of building and has an array of String as types of jobs as a property.
    Owner
    Owner class is for all people that have name and that are owner of something.
    Playground
    Playground is the subclass of architecture that has a default height value.
    Positioned
    Positioned is the interface for all objects that have a position value.
    Street
    Street is the class that contains and manages all the architectures built on it.
    Street.ArchitectureNotFoundException
    Exception for when an architecture is wanted to be removed from a street but there's no such architecture on the street.
    Street.InvalidPositionException
    Exception for when an architecture is tried to be built outside a street.
    Street.NotEnoughSpaceException
    Exception for when there's not enough space in the street for an instance of architecture build.
    Street.PositionOccupiedException
    Exception for when there's another architecture in the street for an instance of architecture build at a given position.
    Street.Side
    Side is the enum for setting apart the architectures on a street that are built on different sides of it
    Time
    Time keeps three integer values as hours, minutes, and seconds.
    Util
    Util class consists of static functions that are used several times in the project and don't really need or have a context or a relation to any user-written class.
